parameters:
To think there's a door that won't open even from
the inside.

Magicians are always such unpleasant people,
aren't they?
I don't think that's true, though.

How did you open the door to the student council
room?

The door was locked with magic, so I investigated
and unlocked it.
I think this place is probably the same.
To think it can be opened with the same magic...
Of course. Otherwise, it wouldn't make sense.
I wonder if it's locked with a different magic.
Hmm, there seems to be a screw here.
Hmm... but I can't move it at all.

No, it's not a matter of strength, it seems to be
locked with magic.

Could it be that it will open if I turn this
screw?

There is a possibility. There doesn't seem to be
any other mechanism in particular.

Blocking passage with a magic that only I know is
a common mechanism in the magician's workshop.

But, if it's the library of this academy, there
might be hints to unlock the magic.
Okay. Then let's head back around here for today.

(I want to proceed as soon as possible... but
there's no helping it, I guess)

There's a teleportation stone here too. It used to
be used in the past, you know.

In this academy, there are many spaces that were
created by magic and then discarded.

It might be the Student Council room. I wonder why
they made it off-limits.

If it's going to be sealed, it's usually something
related to forbidden magic or demons.

The Student Council President... But I'm pretty
sure the last president was a hero.
I don't know the actual truth.

The more exceptional a magician is, the more
likely they are to break taboos.

The magic that is designated as forbidden is
usually very powerful.

(When it comes to the person I love, I can't
afford to be concerned about appearances)
I'm counting on you for the magic.

It's locked. I need to find a magic spell to open
it. For now, maybe I should attend the class on
Hell History before thinking about it.
It opened. Is this kind of magic really okay?
Maybe it's not really closed for real.

Inside the dungeon, there are also trials prepared
to search for those with potential.
Hmm, I wonder what's ahead if that's the case.
I don't know. But I have to make sure.

Is there a reason for this? It doesn't seem like
just mere curiosity.
...My grandfather was a student at this academy.

In the Kingdom of Greatland, he was a famous
magician in many ways.

I was imprisoned and spent the rest of my life in
prison.

And it seems that I have been conducting research
on forbidden magic since my time at the Magic
Academy.

So, somewhere in this academy, there is my
grandfather's workshop.

So, that means it's a workshop where forbidden
magic was being researched... Why would you want
to find something like that?

I won't do anything. I'll just report it to the
academy.

Of course. I don't like the methods of the Church
or the Hero's Church, but I also think it's too
dangerous.

Forbidden magic is not something that can be
controlled by humans.

Olivia's vice president grandfather might have had
some reason as well.

Like wanting to help someone... or to defeat
demons.

Even so, it doesn't become a valid reason to break
taboos.
There is always a price for forbidden magic.
In the end, it leads the user to ruin.
It's rare for you to say something like that.
Well... but there's no deeper meaning to it.
Registered on the dungeon teleportation stone.
MasamuneShall we call it a day?
particle play warp_red_cp player def above
particle play warp_red_cp player def above
No... I was talking to someone in my class.
We're wasting time, let's go already.
Oh, please let me change clothes before that.

...  Note: The ellipsis (...) indicates a pause or
hesitation in speech.

It's a magical tool to increase magical power. It
has an amazing effect, you know.
Well... if you're okay with it, I don't mind.
(Why... is there an ero mark on the piercing...)

Both the piercing and the one on my stomach are to
increase my magical power.

So... it would be helpful if you didn't get too
repulsed.
It's not like I'm repulsed or anything...
That's just how serious Amelia is...

(Honestly, I'm still shaken... I wonder if I
should stop right away)
(But my words won't reach Amelia right now)

(So, I want her to know that I'm not just someone
who needs protection)

[Masamune] Are you also a member of the Magic
Research Club?

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] Indeed, I am Sylvester
von Weisshwaik, a noble of the Kingdom of
Prussia.

[Masamune] No, that doesn't matter. Sorry, but
could you pretend you didn't see anything?

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] Oh, if it isn't
unfamiliar faces. You're not members of the Magic
Research Club, are you?

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] However, that doesn't
matter. Would you like to buy the magic potion I
developed?

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] You'll be amazed by
how incredible it is.
[Masamune] I don't need any magic potion.

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] I followed you
secretly, but I want to go home now...

[Sylvester von Weisshwaik] Being a noble is just
a lie... I'm just an ordinary person who admired
the prince~

Masamune found an advanced thunder magic grimoire!
Masamune learned the spell Thunderbolt!
HP and MP have been fully restored!
HP and MP have been fully restored!

Description MonkeyThere are many lightning
attribute monsters around here. I want to defeat
them with fire magic.

[Olivia] There are a lot of strong monsters here,
so it can't be helped.

[Olivia] I don't think an ordinary student could
defeat even one of them.

[Amelia] Hehe, you've become stronger without me
realizing it.

[Amelia] I... I've been feeling a bit off lately.
It feels like my magical power has been
decreasing...

[Masamune] (I'm not sure of the exact cause, but
it's probably because we've been repeating the
loop)

[Amelia] Maybe I should ask Masamune-kun for some
magical power...

[Amelia] Just kidding... but, can I have your
semen?
[Amelia] Hehe, that was a joke. A kiss will do.

[Amelia] Make sure to let me drink your
saliva...
[Amelia] Phew, I wonder if I've recovered a bit.
